Compared with the rest of the world, the situation in the Czech Republic is not improving at all.
According to the World Bank, the Czech Republic ranks 74th in terms of business conditions, up 8 places from last year.
The Absurdity of the Year contest was first launched in 2006 and continues every year according to the same scenario.
Anyone can report on the administrative and bureaucratic absurdities from April to the end of September each year, the last deadline before the contest closes.
The organisers of the contest then select seven candidates for the "antiprix" and let the public vote during the month of October on the website www.firmaroku.cz/absurdita and on www.ihned.cz.
