The Americans have a new "smart weapon"
The U.S. military has sent to Afghanistan a new "smart" weapon, known only by the code name XM-25.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will influence the conflict there with the Taliban and "will change the game" in their favor.
The new weapon is like a super-precise cannon.
Its projectiles are laser-guided with a precision of a few meters.
The special 25mm caliber ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly explosive explosive, actually works like small grenades.
You can program the munitions so that they will explode on contact with the target but also at any point in their ballistic trajectory.
So it can be used against an enemy hiding behind a barrier, wall, or ditch.
It also has no protection from above, and when a deadly shower of steel shards falls on it, it can be knocked out of the fight as well.
According to Richard Audette who was involved in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon to use "smart" technology.
"The soldier basically uses it in such a way that he finds the target, sends a laser beam to it that determines the distance, thus obtaining a precise aiming point, according to which he corrects his aim to the site and presses the trigger.
"Let's say you aimed at 543 meters".
"When you pull the trigger, the gun charges and fires at a distance of 1, 2, 3 meters, or 543 meters", Audette said.
